4.40	Reefton	Reefton	Reefton is a small town on New Zealand's West Coast region, some 80 km northeast of Greymouth, in the valley of the Inangahua River. State Highway 7 passes through the southern part of the town, and State Highway 69 runs north to connect to State Highway 6. Ahaura is 44 km south-west of Reefton, Inangahua Junction is 34 km to the north, Maruia is 63 km to the east, and the Lewis Pass is 66 km to the south-east.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/2b/Reefton09.jpg/250px-Reefton09.jpg
